                            <comment id="14498385" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Thu, 16 Apr 2015 17:54:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks like this bug was introduced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-7380&quot; title=&quot;runtimeLib SearchComponents will fail if SearchHandler loads them at inform()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-7380&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-7380&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, which hasn&apos;t been released yet.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14498863" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Thu, 16 Apr 2015 22:23:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here&apos;s a patch that fixes the issue by using a volatile.  It also tries to minimize the number of volatile reads by caching in a local variable at the start of handleRequestBody&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
